24/06/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Simitis departs Tuesday (24 June) for Washington to take part, in his capacity as European Council president, in the regular EU-US summit. He will also meet with US President George W Bush. The two leaders are expected to discuss developments in Iraq and the Middle East, the Cyprus issue, non-proliferation of weapons of mass destruction and the global effort against terrorism. (MPA - 23/06/03)
